### Integrate Sanity Studio into Astro Configuration

Source: https://github.com/sanity-io/sanity-astro/blob/main/README.md

This snippet shows how to modify `astro.config.mjs` to integrate Sanity Studio. It imports and adds the `@sanity/astro` integration, specifying `projectId`, `dataset`, `useCdn`, and `studioBasePath` for accessing the Studio. It also highlights the necessity of the `@astrojs/react` integration.

```javascript
// astro.config.mjs
import sanity from '@sanity/astro'
import {defineConfig} from 'astro/config'
import react from '@astrojs/react'

export default defineConfig({
  integrations: [
    sanity({
      projectId: '3do82whm',
      dataset: 'next',
      // Set useCdn to false if you're building statically.
      useCdn: false,
      // Access the Studio on your.url/admin
      studioBasePath: '/admin'
    }),
    react()
  ]
})
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Sanity Integration with Stega for Studio URL

Source: https://github.com/sanity-io/sanity-astro/blob/main/packages/sanity-astro/README.md

This configuration snippet shows how to enable Stega within the Sanity integration in `astro.config.mjs`. It sets the `studioUrl` to the same relative path as `studioBasePath`, allowing Stega to function correctly when Studio runs on an Astro route.

```js
export default defineConfig({
  integrations: [
    sanity({
      studioBasePath: '/admin',
      stega: {
        studioUrl: '/admin',
      },
    }),
  ],
})
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Astro for Server-Side Rendering and Sanity Integration

Source: https://github.com/sanity-io/sanity-astro/blob/main/README.md

This configuration snippet for `astro.config.mjs` sets up an Astro project for server-side rendering (SSR) using the Vercel adapter and integrates the Sanity module. SSR is a prerequisite for Visual Editing functionality.

```js
import vercel from '@astrojs/vercel'

// astro.config.mjs
export default defineConfig({
  integrations: [
    sanity({
      useCdn: true,
      // ...
    }),
    // ...
  ],
  output: 'server',
  adapter: vercel(),
})
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Sanity Client in Astro Project

Source: https://github.com/sanity-io/sanity-astro/blob/main/README.md

Configure the Sanity integration in `astro.config.mjs` by importing `sanity` and `defineConfig`. Provide your `projectId` and `dataset`, and optionally set `useCdn` to `false` for static builds, mirroring `@sanity/client` options.

```typescript
import sanity from '@sanity/astro'
import {defineConfig} from 'astro/config'

// https://astro.build/config
export default defineConfig({
  integrations: [
    sanity({
      projectId: '<YOUR-PROJECT-ID>',
      dataset: '<YOUR-DATASET-NAME>',
      // Set useCdn to false if you're building statically.
      useCdn: false,
    }),
  ],
})
```

--------------------------------

### Create `loadQuery` Helper for Sanity Visual Editing Data

Source: https://github.com/sanity-io/sanity-astro/blob/main/packages/sanity-astro/README.md

This TypeScript helper function, `loadQuery`, is designed to fetch data from Sanity with support for Visual Editing and Stega. It dynamically sets the `perspective` to 'drafts' and includes `resultSourceMap` and a read `token` when Visual Editing is enabled, ensuring live preview functionality.

```ts
// load-query.ts
import {type QueryParams} from 'sanity'
import {sanityClient} from 'sanity:client'

const visualEditingEnabled = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_SANITY_VISUAL_EDITING_ENABLED === 'true'
const token = import.meta.env.SANITY_API_READ_TOKEN

export async function loadQuery<QueryResponse>({
  query,
  params,
}: {
  query: string
  params?: QueryParams
}) {
  if (visualEditingEnabled && !token) {
    throw new Error(
      'The `SANITY_API_READ_TOKEN` environment variable is required during Visual Editing.',
    )
  }

  const perspective = visualEditingEnabled ? 'drafts' : 'published'

  const {result, resultSourceMap} = await sanityClient.fetch<QueryResponse>(query, params ?? {}, {
    filterResponse: false,
    perspective,
    resultSourceMap: visualEditingEnabled ? 'withKeyArraySelector' : false,
    stega: visualEditingEnabled,
    ...(visualEditingEnabled ? {token} : {}),
    useCdn: !visualEditingEnabled,
  })

  return {
    data: result,
    sourceMap: resultSourceMap,
    perspective,
  }
}
```

